    <item>
      <title>Cook or Conserve? A Van Life Power Decision Guide for Electric Cooking Days</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cook-or-conserve-power-decision-guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cook-or-conserve-power-decision-guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Cook or Conserve? A Van Life Power Decision Guide for Electric Cooking Days&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;cook-or-conserve-a-van-life-power-decision-guide-for-electric-cooking-days&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#cook-or-conserve-a-van-life-power-decision-guide-for-electric-cooking-days&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Electric cooking is not just a load decision. It is a recovery decision. The question is not only “can I cook now?” The real question is &lt;strong&gt;“what does this cost my stability tomorrow?”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Cooking &#43; Hot Water Power Stability: Avoid Spike Drift in Van Life</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/cooking-and-hot-water-power-stability/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/cooking-and-hot-water-power-stability/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Cooking and hot-water use can create spike days that quietly push your system into drift.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page keeps it recovery-first: protect baseline, reduce spike-driven drift, and plan refill windows so meals do not become panic decisions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Start here:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/van-battery-drift-diagnosis/&#34; &gt;Van Battery Drift Diagnosis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/van-power-stability-scorecard/&#34; &gt;Van Power Stability Scorecard&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The spike-drift pattern (what people mistake)&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;the-spike-drift-pattern-what-people-mistake&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#the-spike-drift-pattern-what-people-mistake&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Spike drift usually comes from timing and constraints, not one bad appliance choice:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
